1
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:12,291
♪

2
00:00:12,375 --> 00:00:14,291
Don't worry.
Everything will be fine.

3
00:00:14,375 --> 00:00:15,666
Yeah, that's right.

4
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:17,791
Yumi's more than capable
of winning this thing.

5
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:19,500
[ASUKA]
They don't get it.

6
00:00:19,583 --> 00:00:21,291
That's not what I meant!

7
00:00:21,375 --> 00:00:23,333
Because Yumi doesn't know
the truth yet.

8
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:25,625
No.

9
00:00:25,708 --> 00:00:27,708
None of these girls
truly understand.

10
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:34,125
[YUMI] I know the purpose
of the Shinobi Masters.

11
00:00:34,208 --> 00:00:35,375
However...

12
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:38,250
I still object
to your views of justice.

13
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,625
Our beliefs are
far too different.

14
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:44,833
So, what exactly
do you plan on doing?

15
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:47,500
I'm going to fight you
and win this battle.

16
00:00:47,583 --> 00:00:49,958
And then I'll show you
a new type of justice,

17
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:51,833
for all shinobi!

18
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:54,166
"The justice of the moon."

19
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,833
Talk about naive.

20
00:00:55,916 --> 00:00:57,583
♪

21
00:00:57,666 --> 00:00:58,833
[gasps]

22
00:00:58,916 --> 00:01:00,208
[YUMI]
Wait.

23
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:01,500
A black fan?

24
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:04,000
Now then...

25
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:06,375
shall we begin?

26
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:45,625
[KAGURA] All this in the name
of Kurokage, huh?

27
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,083
[KAFURU]
Did you know him?

28
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:49,541
The man they're talking about?

29
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:50,791
Sure did!

30
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:53,375
Wasn't he like
Asuka's grandpa's partner

31
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:54,583
or whatever?

32
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:57,291
I only ever heard rumors
about the guy.

33
00:02:57,375 --> 00:02:59,500
Yeah, tell us
what they were like.

34
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,208
Okay.

35
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:03,500
If you want my honest opinion,
they were both pretty stupid.

36
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,458
[HANAMI]
Huh?

37
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:07,375
In a way,
you could also say

38
00:03:07,458 --> 00:03:09,708
they were very pure of heart.

39
00:03:09,791 --> 00:03:11,458
Kind of like clear water.

40
00:03:12,958 --> 00:03:14,916
Never knowing any impurities.

41
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,291
♪

42
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:26,333
[dog barking in distance]

43
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:28,458
[footsteps]

44
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:29,958
[MAN]
Kurokage!

45
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:31,583
Another mission complete, eh?

46
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:34,250
Yep.

47
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:36,333
So then, how about you
and I go grab a drink

48
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:37,541
after the debriefing?

49
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:41,541
You can drop
the pretentious act, Hanzo.

50
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,166
Drinks are something
you get with a friend,

51
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:45,125
and we're not friends.

52
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:46,416
Geez, loosen up.

53
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,750
So yeah, maybe
we're more like rivals.

54
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,916
But that's a type
of friend, right?

55
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,166
Still counts if you ask me.

56
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:54,791
Whatever shuts you up.

57
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:57,833
I'll be waiting for ya!

58
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:04,333
[plays melancholic tune]

59
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:07,250
[PATRONS chattering]

60
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:11,250
♪

61
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:16,000
♪

62
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:17,375
♪

63
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,333
[HANZO]
Ah!

64
00:04:18,416 --> 00:04:20,041
Hey, I'm ready for another!

65
00:04:20,125 --> 00:04:21,291
-[BARTENDER] Sure thing.
-Ha-ha!

66
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:22,958
-Yeah, that's the stuff.
-[liquid pouring]

67
00:04:23,041 --> 00:04:24,166
Thank you!

68
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:27,500
[WOMAN]
Sorry I'm late.

69
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,166
-[KUROKAGE] Yume?
-[giggles]

70
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,583
[HANZO]
I invited her.

71
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:33,791
Here, grab a seat.

72
00:04:33,875 --> 00:04:34,916
-[shuffling]
-[YUME] Thanks so much.

73
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:37,250
[HANZO]
Ah!

74
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,875
Pick your poison.

75
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:40,000
Let's see.

76
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:42,208
Whatever you're drinking.

77
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:43,708
[HANZO]
Whoa, you like this stuff?

78
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:44,625
Hey, bartender!

79
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:45,666
[BARTENDER]
Coming!

80
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,791
[HANZO]
Okay, here's to you!

81
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,208
[KUROKAGE]
To me?

82
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:51,833
Yeah, a toast
to your relationship with Yume.

83
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,125
You're dating, right?

84
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:57,625
We shinobi have our ways
of getting information.

85
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,208
He means me.

86
00:05:00,291 --> 00:05:01,458
[KUROKAGE]
You told him?

87
00:05:01,541 --> 00:05:03,125
Relax, Kurokage.

88
00:05:03,208 --> 00:05:04,458
Just enjoy your drink.

89
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:06,250
Try to unwind
and have some fun.

90
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:08,916
Yeah, why not?

91
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:11,083
[HANZO]
All right.

92
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,708
-Cheers!
-[glasses clink]

93
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:14,083
[MAN 1]
We need some help!

94
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:15,708
[MAN 2]
Put her down over there!

95
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:17,166
[MAN 3]
There's no room!

96
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:18,583
[MAN 2]
Well then, make some room!

97
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:23,416
They fell into a trap
set by evil ninjas.

98
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,583
Hey, wait!

99
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:33,166
[KUROKAGE] If they get you,
get them back.

100
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,333
Since those dirt bags
love traps so much,

101
00:05:35,416 --> 00:05:37,333
I'll show them
what a real one looks like.

102
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:41,166
You can't repay a dirty trick
with more dirty tricks.

103
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,916
[KUROKAGE]
Don't try to stop me!

104
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,500
I'm going to wipe out
every evil ninja.

105
00:05:46,583 --> 00:05:48,291
Can you really call
fighting out of rage

106
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:49,750
and hatred "justice"?

107
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:52,000
This is a dangerous path.

108
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:55,000
If justice goes too far,
it becomes evil.

109
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:56,791
Shut up!

110
00:05:56,875 --> 00:05:59,041
What the hell
would you know about it?

111
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:06,916
Man, poor Kurokage.

112
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,166
His parents were ninjas, too.

113
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,333
But they were captured
by evil shinobi.

114
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:13,291
♪

115
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:16,333
[YUME]
Yes. He's told me about them.

116
00:06:16,416 --> 00:06:19,416
They were both tortured
before being killed.

117
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:22,041
[HANZO]
I get why he hates evil ninjas

118
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:23,791
more than
the average person does.

119
00:06:23,875 --> 00:06:26,708
♪

120
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:28,375
[HANZO]
But that's also why I'm worried

121
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:29,875
about what he'll do next.

122
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,166
♪

123
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:34,041
[footsteps]

124
00:06:34,125 --> 00:06:37,958
♪

125
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:41,000
Who are you?

126
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:42,750
You're all evil.

127
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,041
Die!

128
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:46,833
[sword swishes]

129
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:47,750
[MEN grunting]

130
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:50,458
[grunts]

131
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,791
Now, hold on.

132
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:55,041
This isn't right.

133
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:56,833
I thought you were a good ninja!

134
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:59,125
This isn't sanctioned.
You'll never get away--

135
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:02,500
-[blade strikes]
-[groaning]

136
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:04,833
♪

137
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:13,083
[MINORI]
Hey, that black weapon.

138
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:16,250
Doesn't it kinda look
like Yumi's fan?

139
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,416
Indeed, it does.

140
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,666
[SHIKI]
If I remember correctly,

141
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:22,083
didn't she get hers
from Kurokage himself?

142
00:07:23,083 --> 00:07:25,125
[SENKOU]
This match isn't over yet.

143
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:28,500
Lady Fubuki is even stronger
than we are.

144
00:07:28,583 --> 00:07:29,958
Yeah.

145
00:07:30,041 --> 00:07:34,250
[wind blowing]

146
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:36,458
Ha!

147
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:42,708
[blades clanging]

148
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:44,041
[yells]

149
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:46,250
[chuckles]

150
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,458
Ah, it would seem that Fubuki
has finally begun her match.

151
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:58,041
Whoa. How the heck is a youma
talking like a real person?

152
00:07:58,125 --> 00:08:00,750
[SUZUNE] There have been reports
of youma saying things

153
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,958
that sound like words,
but this is different.

154
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,625
Now what?

155
00:08:04,708 --> 00:08:06,416
It's safe to say
that this youma

156
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,791
is on a completely new level.

157
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:11,083
It's as intelligent as a human.

158
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:13,541
[RYOBI]
No way. That's impossible!

159
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:15,083
[MURASAKI]
Wait, this youma,

160
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:17,250
it smells like a human.

161
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,333
Tell us who you really are!

162
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,041
I see.

163
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:23,750
You must be curious.

164
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:26,166
But seeing as how
you are all shinobi,

165
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:28,750
you could always try to get
the answer by force.

166
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,416
Unfortunately for you,

167
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,333
that particular action
may result

168
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:33,916
in your untimely deaths.

169
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,791
That's the most intense
murderous aura I've ever felt.

170
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:39,250
Yeah, this probably
won't end well for us.

171
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:43,041
Oh! I'm really scared.
I might even pee myself!

172
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:45,041
Allow me to make
the first move.

173
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:46,083
[whooshing]

174
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,791
[SHINOBI screaming, grunting]

175
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,916
-[blades clanging]
-[YUMI grunting]

176
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:55,833
-Ah!
-[tinkling]

177
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:57,041
[screams]

178
00:08:57,125 --> 00:08:58,041
[chuckles]

179
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,541
♪

180
00:08:59,625 --> 00:09:00,708
[grunts]

181
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:03,750
Secret Ninja Art!

182
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:04,791
Black Ice!

183
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:07,416
[whooshing]

184
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,083
[ice shatters]

185
00:09:13,416 --> 00:09:14,958
She's so strong.

186
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,083
Poor Yumi.

187
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:17,625
Is something wrong?

188
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:19,583
Don't tell me
you're tired already.

189
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:21,375
[breathing heavily]

190
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:22,708
Not even close!

191
00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:25,125
Well then.

192
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:28,166
I'll stop holding back.

193
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:30,625
♪

194
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,416
[wind whooshing]

195
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,625
[FUBUKI grunts]

196
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:39,208
♪

197
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,708
[wind whooshing]

198
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:46,125
♪

199
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:48,125
[moans]

200
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:53,625
♪

201
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:55,750
Wait, what's this form?

202
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:59,166
Ultimate Secret Ninja Art:

203
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,125
Ice Queen!

204
00:10:01,208 --> 00:10:05,458
♪

205
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:12,041
♪

206
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:15,875
This technique carries
Grandfather's hopes and dreams.

207
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,458
Take a good look.

208
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:18,708
It's over!

209
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,375
[KUROKAGE]
You're banishing me?

210
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:23,458
[MASTER 1] You were the one
who attacked evil ninjas

211
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:24,916
when you weren't on a mission.

212
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,791
It's only natural
there would be consequences.

213
00:10:27,875 --> 00:10:31,125
[MASTER 2] As of this moment,
you are relieved of your duties.

214
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,416
[KUROKAGE] Evil ninjas
are our sworn enemies.

215
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:36,000
And it is my duty
as a good shinobi

216
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:38,166
to destroy evil
regardless of our orders.

217
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:40,833
[MASTER 1] Your recklessness
is a result of your youth.

218
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,291
[MASTER 2]
Unless you know of the youma,

219
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,458
it is not your place
to act without permission.

220
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:46,958
[MASTER 3] Indeed,
your ignorance affects us all.

221
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,750
[KUROKAGE]
What are you talking about?

222
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,125
What's a youma?

223
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:52,625
[MASTER 2] There are
certain important members

224
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:55,083
of the shinobi world
who are considered gray,

225
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:57,875
which means they are
neither good nor evil.

226
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,416
[MASTER 1] There are times
when good and evil

227
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:00,875
must help one another.

228
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:02,666
In fact, the world
of the shinobi

229
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:04,708
is connected
more than you know.

230
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:06,416
[MASTER 3]
Yes, and white and black

231
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,750
will occasionally mingle
to form gray.

232
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:11,583
Those were the shinobi
you ignorantly attacked.

233
00:11:11,666 --> 00:11:15,375
So what you're saying
is they get a free pass?

234
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:18,875
[MASTER 2] Listen, we admire
the talent you wield as a ninja.

235
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:21,125
But that doesn't mean
you can ignore our orders

236
00:11:21,208 --> 00:11:22,291
or the way of the shinobi.

237
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:23,791
-[sword whooshes]
-[curtain rustles]

238
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:25,250
That's enough!

239
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,625
Everything but justice is evil!

240
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:30,125
They deserve to die!

241
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:32,291
If you refuse to accept
the punishment

242
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:33,791
we've decided upon,

243
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:37,000
then we'll have to discipline
Hanzo and Yume too.

244
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:39,250
It would be easy
to find something

245
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:40,416
to convict them of.

246
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:41,750
You bastards.

247
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:45,416
You're... all... evil!

248
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:50,083
Yume and Hanzo
had nothing to do with this.

249
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:52,166
Leave them alone!

250
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:56,416
♪

251
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,791
[HANZO] Look, I know
you're in a bad place.

252
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:03,541
But honestly, in my opinion,

253
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:05,625
I think the act
of eliminating evil

254
00:12:05,708 --> 00:12:07,791
is evil within itself.

255
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:08,958
-[fist thumps]
-[glasses clink]

256
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:10,625
-[PATRONS gasp]
-[KUROKAGE] Hanzo!

257
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:13,500
What the hell?
Are you calling me evil?

258
00:12:13,583 --> 00:12:15,458
My parents have been murdered!

259
00:12:15,541 --> 00:12:17,000
My friends have been killed!

260
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,541
You don't get to judge me!

261
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,083
So just back off!

262
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:22,833
[breathing heavily]

263
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:24,958
[HANZO] Listen,
whether you like it or not,

264
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:27,041
all humans have evil
inside of them.

265
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:29,916
You're not the exception,
do you understand that?

266
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,541
Get it through your head!

267
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:33,833
[grunts]
You know what, whatever!

268
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:35,541
I'll just have to make
a new world, then!

269
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:38,500
One that's devoid of evil
and is only good!

270
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,208
[HANZO]
That's impossible, you idiot!

271
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:41,791
You don't get it!
[grunts]

272
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:43,291
But I do.

273
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:45,375
That world.
It's a dream!

274
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:48,125
-[HANZO grunts]
-[boxes clatter, bottles clink]

275
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:50,458
[breathing heavily

276
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:51,666
[groaning]

277
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:52,583
[footsteps]

278
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:53,958
[KUROKAGE]
Hanzo.

279
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:55,375
Just wait.

280
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:57,041
I'll make it a reality.

281
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:01,166
No matter what,

282
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:03,500
I'll create a world
of pure good.

283
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:07,250
Yume.

284
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:12,250
[HANZO]
Kurokage!

285
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:16,583
Don't forget about
the sword and the shield.

286
00:13:17,916 --> 00:13:20,291
I know you'll come
to understand their meaning.

287
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,916
[footsteps]

288
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:38,416
[HANZO] After he parted ways
with the good ninjas,

289
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:42,541
Kurokage began to hunt down
those who were evil on his own.

290
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:43,958
-Of course...
-[KUROKAGE plays harmonica]

291
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:46,375
...this wasn't something
that could be allowed.

292
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:48,791
It wasn't long before
both good and evil ninjas

293
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:50,375
began looking for him.

294
00:13:50,458 --> 00:13:52,166
His life was in grave danger.

295
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:54,833
♪

296
00:13:58,125 --> 00:13:59,750
[chuckles]

297
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,041
Hey, Yume.

298
00:14:01,125 --> 00:14:04,041
You're looking just
as healthy as ever.

299
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:05,625
Thanks.
[laughs]

300
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:10,875
Uh!

301
00:14:10,958 --> 00:14:12,833
Sorry, I didn't mean
to interrupt.

302
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:14,541
[laughs]

303
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:17,541
[HANZO] Oh, I, uh,
brought you some supplies.

304
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:19,583
Thanks for being
so helpful.

305
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:22,250
Sure. Really,
I should apologize.

306
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,583
I wish there was
so much more I could do.

307
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,000
Have you heard anything
from Kurokage?

308
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:29,916
[YUME]
No.

309
00:14:30,916 --> 00:14:31,791
Of course not.

310
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:33,666
[YUME]
Hanzo.

311
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:37,083
I believe that he's still alive.

312
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:40,375
I know in my heart that
he's out there somewhere.

313
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:41,333
Yes.

314
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:42,916
I think so, too.

315
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:48,000
[YUME] I'm going to raise
these children to be shinobi.

316
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:52,541
He may behave foolishly.

317
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,583
But he is still honorable.

318
00:14:54,666 --> 00:14:56,083
They should know that.

319
00:14:56,166 --> 00:14:58,666
And if I pass on
their father's legacy,

320
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,333
they'll learn
to be proud of him.

321
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,041
Yeah.

322
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:05,041
You're right.

323
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:07,708
I'm sure of it.

324
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:12,916
♪

325
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,041
[body thuds]

326
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:21,750
♪

327
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:35,291
♪

328
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:53,666
♪

329
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:56,041
[clinks]

330
00:15:56,125 --> 00:16:00,875
♪

331
00:16:00,958 --> 00:16:02,416
[MAN 4]
He was a talented shinobi...

332
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,625
[footsteps]

333
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,250
...but because
he was Kurokage's son,

334
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,125
he always got
the hardest missions.

335
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:08,375
[MAN 5]
And his wife.

336
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:10,333
For her to die too.

337
00:16:10,416 --> 00:16:11,458
So sad.

338
00:16:11,541 --> 00:16:13,000
[MAN 6]
What about the daughter?

339
00:16:13,083 --> 00:16:15,083
I heard she has
no surviving relatives.

340
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:19,833
[KUROKAGE] My son
and my daughter-in-law are dead.

341
00:16:19,916 --> 00:16:23,208
And I never even saw them
in the flesh.

342
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:26,458
So this is the result
of the path I've chosen.

343
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,375
[YUMI]
One, two, three!

344
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:36,500
One, two, three!

345
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:45,000
♪

346
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,000
I'm so sorry.

347
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,291
Are you all alone?

348
00:16:53,375 --> 00:16:54,208
I am.

349
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,458
What now?

350
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:57,750
Where will you go?

351
00:16:58,791 --> 00:17:00,708
I'm not really sure.

352
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:03,500
I just know that I want
to be a shinobi.

353
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:06,000
A good one, like my mom
and dad were.

354
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,041
[KUROKAGE]
I see.

355
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:13,958
You're sad, aren't you?

356
00:17:15,375 --> 00:17:16,291
[YUMI]
Huh?

357
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:17,750
You're not letting it show,

358
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,291
but I can sense it in you.

359
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:23,458
I've lived most my life
the same way.

360
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,208
Hiding my sorrow behind anger.

361
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,916
I'm your grandfather, Yumi.

362
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,333
But of course

363
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:33,250
I don't expect you
to believe that.

364
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:36,000
[YUMI]
My father and my grandmother

365
00:17:36,083 --> 00:17:38,583
told me my grandfather
had a scar.

366
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:42,000
A big one, right on his cheek,
just like the one you have.

367
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:43,708
They always said

368
00:17:43,791 --> 00:17:46,333
that he was also
a very good Shinobi

369
00:17:46,416 --> 00:17:48,541
and super talented too.

370
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:50,083
They looked really proud

371
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:51,916
every time
they talked about him.

372
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:54,291
But...

373
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:57,083
I think they were also
kind of sad too.

374
00:17:57,166 --> 00:17:58,208
♪

375
00:17:58,291 --> 00:18:00,125
[cries softly]

376
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:01,500
Huh?

377
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:04,416
Excuse me,
but why are you crying, sir?

378
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,291
♪

379
00:18:07,375 --> 00:18:08,666
[KUROKAGE]
Actually...

380
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,125
I'm not sure.

381
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:11,958
♪

382
00:18:12,041 --> 00:18:13,166
[KUROKAGE]
Yumi.

383
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:14,083
Uh?

384
00:18:15,375 --> 00:18:17,291
Will you come
with your grandfather?

385
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:19,625
♪

386
00:18:19,708 --> 00:18:20,583
Hmm.

387
00:18:22,375 --> 00:18:28,458
♪

388
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:29,541
Yes.

389
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:32,791
[KUROKAGE]
Yumi.

390
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:36,291
Your hands are so warm
and full of life.

391
00:18:36,375 --> 00:18:38,166
[YUMI]
So are yours,

392
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:39,750
Grandfather Kurokage.

393
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,083
[KUROKAGE]
Are they, now?

394
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:47,208
[BOTH grunt]

395
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:48,541
[BOTH gasp]

396
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:49,708
Lady Fubuki!

397
00:18:49,791 --> 00:18:51,208
[YUMI]
Stand down.

398
00:18:51,291 --> 00:18:52,666
The battle is over.

399
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,458
Accept that I've defeated you.

400
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:58,583
[FUBUKI laughing]

401
00:18:58,666 --> 00:19:00,958
[YUMI]
Why are you laughing?

402
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:04,375
Because it's so delightful that
you think you've won this match.

403
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:06,208
The fight has just begun.

404
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:08,000
And I don't think
you're prepared.

405
00:19:09,541 --> 00:19:11,958
[FUBUKI]
Shinobi Transformation.

406
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:13,541
-[whooshing]
-[snap]

407
00:19:15,416 --> 00:19:16,250
[moans]

408
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,458
[bands creaking]

409
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,375
Now then...

410
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:30,000
come and get me.

411
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:31,708
[grunts]

412
00:19:33,166 --> 00:19:34,458
[chuckles]

413
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,458
Is that the attack
you thought would beat me?

414
00:19:36,541 --> 00:19:37,541
-[blades clanging]
-[giggles]

415
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:38,708
How sad!

416
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:42,791
Not good.
She's on the run.

417
00:19:42,875 --> 00:19:45,125
That transformation
must have a time limit, right?

418
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:46,541
I'm starting to get worried,

419
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:48,708
Yumi needs to end this
right now!

420
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:50,458
[YUMI groans]

421
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:51,416
[sword shatters]

422
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,916
-[YUMI gasps]
-[grunts]

423
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
-[whooshing]
-[gasps]

424
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:56,000
[screams]

425
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:58,166
[ALL gasp]

426
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:01,791
[ASUKA]
Yumi!

427
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:06,958
Oh, no.

428
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:08,666
[MINORI]
Impossible.

429
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,666
[SHIKI]
Yumi... lost the fight?

430
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:11,750
[moans]

431
00:20:18,125 --> 00:20:19,791
Wait, I remember now.

432
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:20,916
You were there!

433
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:23,416
[KUROKAGE]
Yumi.

434
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,916
I'd like you to meet someone

435
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,583
who's going to be living
with us from now on.

436
00:20:27,666 --> 00:20:29,916
Please think of her
as an older sister.

437
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:33,000
[FUBUKI]
That's right.

438
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:35,083
I lived with you
when you were young.

439
00:20:35,166 --> 00:20:36,333
We trained together.

440
00:20:37,416 --> 00:20:39,666
With Grandfather Kurokage.

441
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,833
Wait, if that's true,

442
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:42,250
then it had
to have been sometime

443
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:44,375
before he took us in
and started training us.

444
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:45,916
You're right.

445
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,208
I feel like I'd remember
if I'd ever met anyone like her.

446
00:20:49,291 --> 00:20:52,375
If you think about it,
you and I are like sisters.

447
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:55,708
Only... we've followed
two very different paths.

448
00:20:55,791 --> 00:20:57,833
There's too much
that you don't know.

449
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,208
That's why
you can still talk about

450
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:02,666
"the justice
of the moon" seriously.

451
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:05,708
Listen well.

452
00:21:05,791 --> 00:21:07,833
I now declare war

453
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:10,833
on every last shinobi
in this world.

454
00:21:10,916 --> 00:21:12,958
Oh, wow.
So that's her goal.

455
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:15,083
What do you mean
when you say "war"?

456
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:17,208
Lady Fubuki.

457
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:19,208
You didn't tell us
about this part.

458
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:22,208
The shinobi are nothing
but hypocrites.

459
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,166
But...

460
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:26,708
that won't matter
once you don't exist.

461
00:21:26,791 --> 00:21:29,958
[rumbling]

462
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:31,458
Everyone!

463
00:21:31,541 --> 00:21:32,708
[grunting]

464
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,166
Wait, Homura?

465
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,791
And Miyabi!

466
00:21:35,875 --> 00:21:37,708
Watch out!
There's a youma coming!

467
00:21:37,791 --> 00:21:39,291
♪

468
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:41,583
[whooshing]

469
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:47,708
[gasps]

470
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:49,500
A youma?

471
00:21:49,583 --> 00:21:51,083
But why?

472
00:21:51,166 --> 00:21:53,375
My intention is
to eliminate both good

473
00:21:53,458 --> 00:21:55,708
and evil shinobi alike.

474
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:58,166
With this, my blade of revenge.

475
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:00,625
Not to mention,

476
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:02,416
this ferocious youma!

477
00:23:33,291 --> 00:23:35,333
The reason should be obvious.

478
00:23:35,416 --> 00:23:37,541
The youma are a threat
to everything in this world,

479
00:23:37,625 --> 00:23:39,041
and that includes humanity!

480
00:23:39,125 --> 00:23:41,875
The door to another realm
is now open.

481
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:43,333
♪

482
00:23:43,416 --> 00:23:46,291
Finally, the fun can begin.

483
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:48,208
-[ASUKA screams]
-[laughing]

